<div style="margin-bottom:60px;">Hello, there! My name is Amy. I'm 16 and currently a senior in high school. I was born in Guangzhou and raised in New York City. My current fandoms are (but not limited to!) Persona 5, Yuri on Ice, Gintama, Mystic Messenger, and Katekyo Hitman Reborn. I procrastinate 24/7 by watching (but never finishing) Korean dramas & Japanese cartoons + reading fanfiction & webtoons. I also occasionally play visual novels.<p>On a side note, I'll be applying to university this year which means that there will be times when I won't be able to put out new content and answer questions.

</div>

<span class="title">How It All Started</span>
I wrote my very first line of code way back when I made my Tumblr blog in 2014 and saw how hideous the default Tumblr theme (Optica) looked. Granted, getting rid of the header and changing the font size wasn't really a big deal but soon after, I stumbled upon <a href="http://theme-hunter.tumblr.com/">theme-hunter</a>, a resource blog that showcased Tumblr themes created by various bloggers, and immediately decided that I would learn how to create one for my own blog.<p>I started messing around with HTML and CSS and worked with base codes until I was able to create a theme from scratch. During this time, I released a number of themes under a couple of URLS but it wasn't until after completing the <a href="https://girlswhocode.com/">GirlsWhoCode Summer Immersion Porgram</a> that I began posting my content on Nemurou.<p>

